  "description": "This quiz assesses proficiency in Node.js I/O, covering fundamental file system tasks, buffer handling, encoding, and advanced streaming techniques. It is moderately challenging, aiming to reinforce best practices for efficient data processing. The tone is encouraging and instructional, guiding learners to deepen their understanding of streams versus buffers.",
  "topics": [
    "Node.js file system (fs) operations",
    "Buffers and encoding",
    "Stream APIs (readable, writable, transform)",
    "Performance and best practices for I/O"
  ],
  "audience": "Developers with basic Node.js experience who want to solidify their I/O knowledge, such as junior to mid‑level backend engineers and students learning server‑side JavaScript."
